\begin_layout Subsection
Warnings/Mistakes to avoid
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
When defining macros, be sure NOT to use names that conflict with existing
 commands.
 For example, naming a macro 
\backslash
section will cause havoc as this name conflicts with the command for the
 heading of sections.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Advice on using typesetting to reduce algebraic errors
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Highlight the changes that will be made in pairs (or more) and use under/over
 braces to show alternate expression of a certain symbol.
 Example:
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{eqnarray*}
h_{SQL} & = & \frac{\overbrace{g_{SQL}}^{\sqrt{2\hbar m\Omega^{2}}}}{m\Omega^{2}L/2}=\underrightarrow{2}\frac{\sqrt{\underrightarrow{2}\hbar\underline{m\Omega^{2}}}}{\underline{m\Omega^{2}}\underbrace{L}_{\sqrt{L^{2}}}}\\
 & = & \sqrt{\frac{8\hbar}{m\Omega^{2}L^{2}}}
\end{eqnarray*}

\end_inset

(Note there seems to be a problem with 
\backslash
undertilde at the moment: it is underfined; missing tex package??)
\end_layout

